## Comparative Summary of Pros and Cons

| Aspect                     | Arguments For Reintroduction                          | Arguments Against Reintroduction                     |
|----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| **Deterrence**             | May deter violent crime; some studies support this | No conclusive evidence; similar or lower murder rates in abolition states |
| **Retribution**            | Provides justice and closure for victims            | Viewed by some as revenge; moral objections         |
| **Incapacitation**         | Permanently removes dangerous offenders              | Life imprisonment also prevents re-offense          |
| **Risk of Error**          | -                                                   | Risk of executing innocent people                    |
| **Cost**                   | Potentially less costly than life imprisonment       | Death penalty cases are more expensive due to appeals |
| **Bias and Fairness**      | -                                                   | Disproportionate impact on minorities and poor       |
| **Ethical Considerations** | Seen as just punishment for heinous crimes           | Violates human rights; considered cruel and unusual  |

